                <note rend="inline" type="source">701.2325/19: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Peru</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Moore</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Lima</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1928-07-17T12:00:00-05:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">July 17, 1928—noon</hi>
                        </date>.<lb/>[Received 2:30 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>77. Department’s 59, July 16, 5 p.m. Saw President Leguia. He says that if our
                    country desires it, he could see no objection to appointment of Ambassadors. It
                    is probable that this question would have to go before Congress which meets July
                    28th.</p>
                <p>The President said he is surprised and delighted at the way the matter has been
                    received in Peru and the world generally.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Moore</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
